# URL of the backend signaling server.
# For local development the defaults below work out of the box.
#
# In production (e.g. Render) these values are pre-configured in
# .env.production and will be baked into the Vite build automatically.
# You can override them by setting the variables in your Render service's
# "Environment" tab — Render build-time env vars take precedence over
# .env.production.
#
# Example override for a different deployment:
#   VITE_SOCKET_URL=https://my-backend.onrender.com
VITE_BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:4000
VITE_SOCKET_URL=http://localhost:4000

# ── Notes ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Both variables must use HTTPS in production.
# Neither value should contain a wildcard (*).
# This file is safe to commit; the actual .env file must NOT be committed.

